</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanur>Nanur</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/03 2:15:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26213.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks to a GM on Tribunal</span><hr size=1> depends on your problem i think. My general experience with GM has not been the best. I was 1018 on my wizard for over 3 hours so when i came back i was dead and was told  byt the GM that i could not get my xp back since the 3 hour timer was gone. Fastforward a few months and i die on my cleric who was on a corpse run. I did take 30pp out of bank to get a trans. The wizard refused payment. SO i have 30pp on me when i die a second time. I return again find my gear corpse but not the nekkid one(except for 30pp). I petition that day and each day for 2 weeks. I never got a response till 2 weeks later. The GM investigates   says the records showed a corpse and it poofed immeditaley after death. He gave my xp back and my 30pp. That was great except for the fact that i  could not be helped in one instance and i was helped in another instance both were verfied game bugs. So you see sometimes they just dont help when they can and sometimes they do help when you get one who know what they can and can NOT do. On legends the greig encounter was respawned when it was lost due to a bug on terris-thule the SERVER GM said mobs can NOT be respawned. I understand not respawning a mob if it does not meet the requirements of a bug etc but do NOT sit there and tell me it can  NOT be done. I hate that. The basic moral of the story all GMs' are not created equal <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nanur>Nanur</A> at: 4/23/03 2:20:06 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mikar>Mikar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/03 8:18:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26213.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks to a GM on Tribunal</span><hr size=1> If you play Euro hours you are SoL. <br>
<br>
I have often had a petition go unanswered for 3+ hours. When a guide did reply I have been told that a GM would be online sometime after 4pm pst .. which is 1am for me.<br>
<br>
Not to say I havent had some good experiences too - but - in particular for those of us that dont play PST the game really needs to display statistics wrt petitions..<br>
<br>
#GMs online<br>
#Guides online on server<br>
#petitions on server<br>
#avg wait time for a reply during last 24 hours<br>
#avg wait time for petitions currently in line<br>
<br>
Also, there *has* to be atleast 1 full GM online at all times - been told that no GM will be online for hours is simply not within the limits of reason.<br>
<br>
As it stands the wait is regularly well and truly beyond the reasonable - yet there is no wait to tell if there is even anyone at all online to answer your petition.  <p>Mikar</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mikar>Mikar</A> at: 4/23/03 8:20:09 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kswilson>kswilson</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#ffffff>(4/23/03 9:45:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26213.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Thanks to a GM on Tribunal</span><hr size=1> I posted this mainly because I don't feel that those GM's that are helpful get enough credit.  I couldn't think of a better way to let her, and maybe her bosses, know how much I appreciate the work she is doing than to post it on a board that many people read.  As I said, the CS definitly has some issues in my opinion.  But I find that more people gripe about it and not enough give positive feedback.  So here is my positive feedback. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
